## Implementation Notes

### Project Structure

```
archon/
├── app.py              # Streamlit entry point
├── pages/              # Multi-page app
│   ├── 1_create.py     # Agent creation wizard
│   ├── 2_test.py       # Agent testing playground
│   └── 3_deploy.py     # Deployment dashboard
├── archon/             # Core logic (UI-independent)
│   ├── builder.py      # Agent construction
│   ├── graph.py        # LangGraph workflows
│   └── memory.py       # Supabase integration
├── .streamlit/
│   └── config.toml     # Theme and settings
└── requirements.txt
```

### Key Dependencies

```
streamlit>=1.30
langchain>=0.1
langgraph>=0.0.20
supabase>=2.0
groq>=0.4
```

### Deployment Options

1. **Development:** Local Streamlit (`streamlit run app.py`)
2. **Demo:** Streamlit Cloud (free tier)
3. **Production:** Docker on Ubuntu VM (if traffic grows)

---

## Review

### Validation Criteria

- [ ] Agent creation workflow functional
- [ ] LangGraph integration working
- [ ] Supabase memory persisting correctly
- [ ] MCP protocol for IDE integration
- [ ] Deployment to Streamlit Cloud successful

### Future Considerations

- **Scale:** If user traffic exceeds Streamlit's capabilities, extract API layer
- **Mobile:** Streamlit mobile experience is acceptable but not ideal
- **Embedding:** May need iframe embedding for external integrations

